[Name] mICQ
[Summary] A portable, small, yet powerful console-based ICQ client.
[License] GNU General Public License (GPL)
[Description] mICQ (Matt's ICQ Clone) is a portable, small, yet powerful
console-based ICQ client. It supports password changing, auto-away,
creation of new accounts, and other features that makes it a very
complete yet simple client.  It is able to send and receive messages
from the ICQ network, list users that are offline and online
(including their online status), search for users by email address,
and look up basic (name, UIN, email) information.
[Homepage] http://www.micq.org/
